## 9. Icon Vertical Centering in Native HTML Elements

When placing an icon inside a native `<span>` or `<div>` alongside an `<input>`, use flexbox on the wrapper rather than CSS `transform: translateY(-50%)`, which may not work correctly in NativeWind's web output:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — flexbox wrapper centers reliably
<span className="absolute left-3 flex items-center justify-center pointer-events-none">
  <SearchIcon size={16} />
</span>

// ❌ BAD — transform may not center correctly in NativeWind
<Icon style={{ position: "absolute", top: "50%", transform: "translateY(-50%)" }} />
```

---

## 12. Match the Source Design — Read Before Building

Before implementing any component (navbar, footer, cards, etc.):
1. **Read the source design** — check the original component file, the design spec, or the app's config
2. **Identify what the component actually needs** — number of menu options, icons, layout, interactions
3. **Build to spec** — don't assume generic defaults (e.g. "always 3 theme options", "always show user icon")

Rules in this file capture *patterns and pitfalls*, not app-specific decisions. App-specific choices (colors, number of menu items, which icons to show) must always come from the source design.

---

## 10. Text Centering — Apply `text-center` Directly on Each `Text`, Not on Parent Box

**Problem:** In NativeWind, `text-center` on a `Box` (which maps to a React Native `View`) does **not** cascade down to child `Text` components. Children appear left-aligned even when the parent has `text-center`.

**Fix:** Add `text-center` directly to every `Text` or `Heading` that needs centering. Use `items-center` on the parent `Box` to center flex children horizontally.

```json
// ❌ BAD — text-center on Box does not cascade
{ "type": "Box", "props": { "className": "text-center" }, "children": [
  { "type": "Text", "text": "This will NOT be centered" }
]}

// ✅ GOOD — text-center on each Text, items-center on Box
{ "type": "Box", "props": { "className": "flex flex-col items-center" }, "children": [
  { "type": "Text", "props": { "className": "text-center" }, "text": "This IS centered" }
]}
```

Use `gap-*` instead of `space-y-*` / margin utilities for spacing between flex children in NativeWind.

